    GetElement<I,E,O>

    public static class GetElement.GetField<I,O>
extends GetElement<I,java.lang.String,O>
    An element accessor that uses reflection to query the value of a certain field in target objects by invoking the associated "get" method. This is done by means of the ReflectUtil.invokePublic(Object, String) method.

    Attention: if the function's output type (O) is not of type Object the property value will be cast to that type at runtime. If it does not match that type a ClassCastException will be thrown.
